  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Performance measurement consists of two practices, a practice for setting up a performance measurement system, and once&#xD;
    that system is set up, a practice for managing it.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    This process is illustrated&#xD;
    below:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img height=&quot;421&quot; alt=&quot;Performance Measurement Process&quot; src=&quot;./resources/perf_meas_process_update.gif&quot; width=&quot;570&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In addition to providing a process framework, this configuration includes detailed guidance on how to choose metrics,&#xD;
    and how to automate metrics reporting.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    An effective performance measurement system should include a systematic approach to improving performance. This&#xD;
    configuration includes guidance on which practices to focus on, as well as which metrics to gather.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    A performance measurement system, however, only evaluates projects from the outside. To drive improvement, you need&#xD;
    team members be able assess themselves and empowered to make improvements. For more on this, see the Practice: Whole&#xD;
    Team and also the IBM service offering for Self Assessments.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
